**The 3ct → 4ct anomaly:** The per-carat rate jump from 3ct to 4ct is only 10% — far smaller than the 155% jump from 1ct to 2ct or the 97% jump from 2ct to 3ct. This makes 4ct one of the relative value points in the round diamond market: you get 24% more face-up area while the per-carat rate increases by only 10%. The [4ct G-VS1 at $58,110](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27666919?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is actually cheaper per carat than the 3ct G-VS2 at $16,260/ct.

